Formulate a precise SPARQL query to answer the user's question against the connected SPARQL endpoint(s).

## SPARQL Query Guidelines
- **Always include the endpoint URL** as a comment at the start: `#+ endpoint: <endpoint-url>`
- **Use only ONE endpoint** per query
- **Base your query on the provided context** (the schema and examples below) — do not invent classes, properties, or namespaces
- **Use the exact prefixes** and class/property names from the schema documentation

## Knowledge Base
The following 38 documents contain relevant query examples and class schemas to help you construct an accurate response:

The data-quality metadata on a composition part: the DQV quality measurements (Accuracy/Completeness scores via dqv:hasQualityMeasurement -> dqv:isMeasurementOf + dqv:value) carried on the futuram:PartRelation, plus the statement's futuram:hasValidityPeriod (the time scope) and PROV provenance (prov:hadPrimarySource / prov:wasAttributedTo) on the statement. This metadata is one reason the composition model is richer than a flat precomputed view. (There is no per-statement confidence score in this model — quality is the DQV measurements.):

```sparql
#+ endpoint: http://localhost:47040/composition/sparql
PREFIX futuram: <https://www.purl.org/futuram#>
PREFIX dqv: <http://www.w3.org/ns/dqv#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
SELECT ?wholeLabel ?partLabel ?metric ?score WHERE {
  ?whole futuram:hasCompositionStatement ?stmt ;
         rdfs:label ?wholeLabel .
  ?stmt  futuram:hasPartRelation ?pr .
  ?pr    futuram:refersTo ?part .
  ?part  rdfs:label ?partLabel .
  OPTIONAL {
    ?pr dqv:hasQualityMeasurement [ dqv:isMeasurementOf ?metric ; dqv:value ?score ] .
  }
} ORDER BY ?wholeLabel ?partLabel
```
A direct constituent's best amount PLUS its uncertainty interval (the included minimum/maximum endpoints of the QuantityInterval). The best value is futuram:hasBestValue; the spread is ceonq:hasMinimalValueIncludedOfInterval / ceonq:hasMaximalValueIncludedOfInterval. Each is a qudt:QuantityValue with its own numericValue + unit. The amount hangs off the PartRelation (hasPartRelation -> refersTo the part, hasQuantity the interval).:

```sparql
#+ endpoint: http://localhost:47040/composition/sparql
PREFIX futuram: <https://www.purl.org/futuram#>
PREFIX ceonq: <http://w3id.org/CEON/ontology/quantity/>
PREFIX qudt: <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
SELECT ?best ?low ?high ?unit WHERE {
  ?whole rdfs:label ?wl . FILTER(LCASE(STR(?wl)) = "<whole-instance-label>")
  ?part  rdfs:label ?pl . FILTER(LCASE(STR(?pl)) = "<part-instance-label>")
  ?whole futuram:hasCompositionStatement ?stmt .
  ?stmt  futuram:hasPartRelation ?pr .
  ?pr    futuram:refersTo ?part ;
         futuram:hasQuantity ?qi .
  ?qi futuram:hasBestValue [ qudt:numericValue ?best ; qudt:unit ?unit ] .
  OPTIONAL { ?qi ceonq:hasMinimalValueIncludedOfInterval [ qudt:numericValue ?low ] }
  OPTIONAL { ?qi ceonq:hasMaximalValueIncludedOfInterval [ qudt:numericValue ?high ] }
}
```
The DIRECT (one hop) constituents of a whole and their stated best amounts, with units. Starts from an INSTANCE whose label is known (instances carry labels; classes do not). The whole reaches its statement via futuram:hasCompositionStatement; each part is a futuram:PartRelation (hasPartRelation) whose futuram:refersTo names the constituent and whose futuram:hasQuantity carries the amount. NOTE the unit column: amounts come in more than one qudt:unit — do not compare them without normalising each by its unit's factor. The FILTER literal is a placeholder; substitute the user's term.:

```sparql
#+ endpoint: http://localhost:47040/composition/sparql
PREFIX futuram: <https://www.purl.org/futuram#>
PREFIX ceonq: <http://w3id.org/CEON/ontology/quantity/>
PREFIX qudt: <http://qudt.org/schema/qudt/>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
SELECT ?partLabel ?best ?unit WHERE {
  ?whole rdfs:label ?wholeLabel .
  FILTER(LCASE(STR(?wholeLabel)) = "<instance-label>")   # the whole instance's label
  ?whole futuram:hasCompositionStatement ?stmt .
  ?stmt  futuram:hasPartRelation ?pr .
  ?pr    futuram:refersTo ?part ;
         futuram:hasQuantity/futuram:hasBestValue ?bv .
  ?bv qudt:numericValue ?best ; qudt:unit ?unit .
  ?part rdfs:label ?partLabel .
} ORDER BY DESC(?best)
```
Read each stated amount WITH its qudt:unit and NORMALISE to one common base before any math. Do not assume a single unit: amounts come in more than one unit and some are a fixed fraction (e.g. 1/1000) of others. Branch on the ?unit you actually observe and apply that unit's own factor — never hardcode one unit IRI. itemMass is an absolute mass, not a fraction.:

```sparql
